channel.title: Is it just me?
channel.description: Or are the tutorials more Java related, but using variables defined in RuneScape private servers? It'd be one hell of a section of people actually read it, that's for sure, but whatever happened to like... The tutorials on how to add stuff? Like when people used to all flip out over dragon smithing. Tutorials with cool shit, like that?

item.title: Is it just me?
item.description:
@11167 wrote:

I understand all of you. But still, looking at some of the tutorials, it looks more like it came off of the Java docs (based on the explanations, where, etc) and just some of the variables are RSPS related. Like, I’m sure that if any of us went to the tutorial section right now, < half of the tutorial titles (unless it’s worse?) will not be related to RSPS.

Basically, we have a situation like `Rich. We need tutorials that actually teach Java, but we also need ones that have true RSPS-content. We can’t have 90% of the latter because they don’t teach anything.
